pageContext.claim: “Wages, wages, beautiful wages for the first time in years, wages are rising. Confidence is soaring.”
pageContext.analysis: Actually, wages began a steady increase in 2014 but for many workers were stagnant in 2017, Trump’s first year in office. Wages grew at an annual rate of 3.1% in October, which was a nine-year high, but not "the first time in years."
